            "answer_text": "I would say.. Ask God - The bible says ask and it shall be given (Don\u2019t misinterpret this as your entitled to whatever you ask)Believe you can work for either of these top wall street banksBuckle down and study (Everything in the sector of the bank you want to go into)Network - LinkedIn, is great\u2026make sure you try your best to show gratitude when someone gives you the time of day to speak to themApply - Stay up to date with their deadlines, if you\u2019re in college they begin recruiting for the following summer as soon as the current summer\u2019s 10 week program is upPassively and actively work on your soft skillsRepeat steps #1 - #6In my experience I did these steps. I studied Computer Science in College and I was offered a Tech role and a Corperate Finance role at the same time. Not to brag or anything but to show you that its possible. I focused heavily on step 1 and 2 because it gave me the daily drive i needed to stay focused and confident despite my lack in merit (I went to an unknown state school, at the time I had very little CS courses (3) under my belt and only 1 Finance course under my belt) Also , I love helping people with anything! That being said feel free to reach out via LinkedIn or on Quora, if you need your resume reviewed or something! ",
