            "answer_text": "There is an answer on quora, and I can in a year or so update this answer with that link to get you the same you could search for. The list of universities that have recruiters from JPM and GS visit is fairly long and comprehensive. Additionally, outside US they recruit in most major countries in Asia and Europe. In India they visit the Top four management schools, IIMs at A, B C and L. (quite a soup, there are 16 other IIMs) and also fairly flexibly for undergraduates, but I would not buy that profile. In Asia, the faster route would be thru education in Singapore, the best if you are choosing a foreign university is still the USA. There are three management schools of note and two of them have quite a rush of offers from Wall Street ( NUS and NTU) ",
